    Another type of tube is one that is  *open* at both ends. Examples are some organ pipes, flutes, and oboes. The resonances of tubes open at both ends can be analyzed in a very similar fashion to those for tubes closed at one end. The air columns in tubes open at both ends have maximum air displacements at both ends, as illustrated in {'Figure_18_5_8a Figure 18.5.8a}. Standing waves form as shown.
    
    
            
    
    Based on the fact that a tube open at both ends has maximum air displacements at both ends, and using {'Figure_18_5_8a Figure 18.5.8a} as a guide, we can see that the resonant frequencies of a tube open at both ends are:
    
